Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds.
Chop into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain the @Mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry
with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}. Preheat the #grill{} to high. Heat a
drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and pepper
chunks. Stir-fry until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils
after handling raw meat.

Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic and @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}.
Cook for ~{30%seconds} more.

Stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g},
@Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. IMPORTANT:
Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and
piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When ready, combine the cooked pasta and sauce (in whichever pan is biggest).
Stir through the @Harissa Paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Add
a splash of @?water{} if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an
appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Scatter over the mozzarella and Cheddar.

Pop the dish under the grill and cook until the cheese is bubbling and golden,
~{7-8%minutes}.

When ready, share the harissa pasta bake between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!